This setup is two rifles in one.  All that is needed is to swap out the bolt and put the other upper on and you can switch from 300 black out to 5.56mm instantly.    Both uppers have Wilson Combat Match Grade Stainless Steel Barrels with a 1:8 twist.  The 300 is a 16’’ barrel and the 5.56mm is a 14.7’’ barrel.  Another upgrade on this rifle is a Hyper touch trigger. Other features include a Troy free floating Rail for the 300 and Magpul green drop in for grips on the 5.56mm.  This set includes a complete set of furniture for each upper.  The 300 has all Flat Dark Earth fixures and the 5.56mm has all green fixtures. Each setup is pictured below. All features are quality and interchangeable.
Finally the Nikon P223 scope with bullet drop compensator is mounted in a one piece Burris P.E.P.E.R mount.  This is a great combo, I have another setup just like this on two of my other rifles.  The one pice mount eliminates tension on the scope tube that you would otherwise get from normal two pice scope rings.  This allows the setup to retain its zero better and increases the life of the scope.  This setup works great for both calibers.

postcontent:
Leupold Mark 4 CQ/T 1-3x14mm optic

This is in great shape, and functions as it should.  I went down a different route with my optic choice, and no longer need this. 
NO BOX




Leupold CQT. The Leupold Mark 4 1-3x14mm CQT is a revolutionary optical sight for tactical firearms such as the AR-15 and M16. Developed in cooperation with both the U.S. military and law enforcement agencies, the Leupold CQT combines the strengths of a red dot sight and a variable power riflescope. Incredibly tough, 100% waterproof, and devastatingly accurate, only the Leupold CQT is ready and able to handle the variety of close-contact situations common to both law enforcement and the military. 

The Circle Dot Reticle
The Circle Dot reticle of the Leupold CQT is designed to offer fast target acquisition in any environment. Reticle is visible without being illuminated. No power is required to see the reticle.

Estimating range using the Circle Dot reticle is simple. Place the target inside the circle of the reticle. At 3x the diameter equates to 6 feet in height at 100 yards. At 200 yards, 6 feet is measured from the dot to the edge of the circle.

Dot Size: 3 MOA at 3x, 9 MOA at 1x.

Circle Size: Edge to edge, the subtension of the circle is 18 inches at 25 yards, or 6 feet at 100 yards when set on 3x. From the center of the dot to the edge of the circle, the subtension is 6 feet at 200 yards when set on 3x.

Circle Line: The width of the line creating the circle is large enough to be easily visible, but thin enough so as not to obliterate an 18-inch object at 500 yards when set on 3x.

Comes with Flat top or carry handle mount, Flip-up lens covers and AA Battery & Battery compartment.

Note: CAN ONLY SHIP TO U.S. AND APO



Features

•True 1x setting functions as your non-magnifying, illuminated sight for tactical scenarios or engaging targets at extremely close range
•2x or 3x settings give you the additional power to accurately engage targets at medium ranges
•Leupold Circle Dot reticle is a bold aiming point for the operator, and also provides range estimation
•1/2-MOA adjustments for windage and elevation
•Ten reticle illumination settings to match any light conditions without overwhelming your natural low-light vision
•Two low-intensity settings work with night-vision devices
•Attach accessories using the integrated MIL-STD-1913 rail mount cross-slots
•Large field of view for fast target acquisition and tracking of moving targets
•One AA battery powers the Leupold CQT for up to 600+ hours at medium setting
•Made in the U.S.A

title: For Sale:  Enfield Mk III* SMLE from Lithgow Armory Australia
postcontent:
Clearing out safe. This is a Enfield Mk III* from Lithgow Armory Australia. Most parts including stock are matching serial numbers, and is dated 1941. Many military stamps and cartouches are from all over the rifle and stock. It has one import stamp on the rear right receiver that is very light and difficult to read, N.A. RDGFLD, NJ. The bore is lightly pitted from the corrosive ammo used during the war, but the rifling is still sharp. May require re-crowning if so desired. Includes military magazine, no paperwork, no ammo

This was the first rifle I ever purchased as a teenager in 1990. At the time I had it checked for proper head spacing at Williams Gun Sight. When I used it, it was still very accurate. As a youngster I carefully painted the some of metal to prevent rust, it can be removed with turpentine, the finish below is thin and worn as would be expected, but no rust. Other then a yearly cleaning and oiling the rifle has not been used since 1991.
I read a little into the markings, history rifle. There are no rejection stamps, It was back at Lithgow Armory in 1946. Matching numbers on bolt, reciever, nose cap, stock and barrel. MA VII markings on band, barrel, receiver I was told meant it was capable of using high velocity ammunition. HV marked barrel rear sight. There are many marking from the Armory and units. While I'm used to working on vintage US rifles many of the markings on this rifle I'm unfamiliar with.

title: For Sale:  Hardly used VEPR Hunter 7.62x54R
postcontent:
Good luck getting another one of these! I got this Molot built 7.62x54R VEPR Hunter from the original owner over a year ago. It had approximately 200 rounds through it when I purchased it, and I have taken it out a total of ONE time, putting another 50 or so rounds down the barrel. All PRVI Partizan, no corrosive ammo. 

For those who don't know the background, this is a premium rifle that was briefly produced by the Molot factory in Russia. It features a 21", chrome lined heavy, fluted barrel with an integrated muzzle brake, walnut stock, and a much nicer trigger than typical AK pattern rifles. The milled receiver and removable trigger pack are completely unique to the Hunter model and of a much higher quality than any other VEPR model. They were deemed too expensive to make a profit by the Molot factory and were discontinued.

It comes with everything it came with from the factory: Rifle, scope mount (never mounted) cleaning rod, and (2) 5-round magazines. The box has seen better days but the rifle is very nice. Any damage is visible in photos. Some kind of mottling to the finish on the bottom of the handguard (on the area that is already textured) and a couple of small nicks to the stock here and there. Bolt carrier and hammer are barely worn, and there are slight rub marks in all the usual places. Probably not even broken in yet!

Let me know if you have any questions or want any other pictures.

Price is $1,400 + actual shipping.

Eric

Like new condition Sig Sauer 556 ER adjustable piston operated Rifle. Very clean and has been sitting in safe for a couple years. Took to range, fired 40 rounds and loved it. Amazing trigger and everything is basically new. I just don't have anywhere to shoot it, I am moving and expecting a new baby. These rifles have all the advantages and durability of a high end milled AK but are a Swiss design. Bolt is an upgraded version of an AK bolt and charge from the side the same way.Firing pin is spring loaded to avoid slamfires. It is basically like a high end milled AK with far nicer fit and finish but in  5.56. I will include a  nib 40 round gen 3 pmag along with the original Sig Sauer 30 round mag and surefire 60 round mag. I also have a 350 dollar set of POF sights on it with dove tail conversion kit. The gun shows almost no wear and has been stored for a while. the only wear is the inherent ejection port wear which in no way effects the functionality of the rifle. Accepts all AR variant mags. Ambdextrious safety and controls. If you can find one of these in the store, it would go for 2000.00 or so plus the extras. The newer ones are no where near as nice. This one produced in 2008 and used twice since. The best factory trigger I have ever felt. 4 position collapsable stock,-Swiss style furniture with rails built in. This is one of the nicer  built ones that did not get recalled. I also have a new in box green laser sight and a decent red dot sight to go with it as well. Will send pics to serious inquiries. I have new lake city ammo to add for the right deal. Will sell rifle alone with Sig mag and red dot sight for 1250 obo.
